'''C sharp''' (C#)

# C# is an object-oriented [[programming language]] developed by [[Microsoft]] Corporation as part of their .NET initiative in response to the success of Sun Microsystems' [[Java]] programming language. C# source code—as well as those of other .NET languages—is compiled into an intermediate byte code called MSIL (Microsoft Intermediate Langauge. C# is primarily derived from the C, C++, and Java programming languages with some features of Microsoft's Visual Basic in the mix. (Courtesy [http://www.csharp-online.net/ CSharp-Online.NET])